Package: ONMixture
Type: Package
Title: ONMixture: Open-population hierarchical Bayesian modeling functions
Version: 0.2.0
Author: Dr. David R. Stewart
Maintainer: <david_stewart@fws.gov>
Description: ONMixture accompanies the San Bernardino Wildlife Refuge Rio Yaqui Fish Pond Sampling Protocol. The first function is fully automated, meaning that it runs two hierarchical Bayesian random effect models. The first is an open population model that estimates population abundance, growth rate, and carrying capacity. The second model estimates how abundance and detection relates to environmental correlates. The second function is a zeros- and ones- inflated Beta-binomial degenerate model that will be used to describe the relationship between percent small fish and environmental correlates. Each function produces either a set of tables or figures and saved to a persons working directory. Those tables and figures should be included in the San Bernardino National Wildlife Refuge 5 year comprehensive reports.
